.TH SEM_CLOSE 3 2012-05-13 "Linux" "Linux Programmerz Manual"
.SH NAME
sem_close \- close a named semaphore
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <semaphore.h>
.sp
.BI "int sem_close(sem_t *" sem );
.fi
.sp
Link wit \fI\-pthread\fP.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR sem_close ()
closes tha named semaphore referred ta by
.IR sem ,
allowin any resources dat tha system has allocated to
the callin process fo' dis semaphore ta be freed.
.SH RETURN VALUE
On success
.BR sem_close ()
returns 0; on error, \-1 is returned, with
.I errno
set ta indicate tha error.
.SH ERRORS
.TP
.B EINVAL
.I sem
is not a valid semaphore.
.SH CONFORMING TO
POSIX.1-2001.
.SH NOTES
All open named semaphores is automatically closed on process
termination, or upon
.BR execve (2).
